    question: "Reduce stream to single value with reduce().",
    mathSolution: "reduce() combines elements using binary operator",
    codeSolution:
      'import java.util.*;\nimport java.util.stream.*;\n\nList<Integer> numbers = Arrays.asList(1, 2, 3, 4, 5);\n\n// Sum with reduce\nint sum = numbers.stream()\n    .reduce(0, (a, b) -> a + b);\nSystem.out.println("Sum: " + sum);\n\n// Sum with method reference\nint sum2 = numbers.stream()\n    .reduce(0, Integer::sum);\nSystem.out.println("Sum (method ref): " + sum2);\n\n// Product\nint product = numbers.stream()\n    .reduce(1, (a, b) -> a * b);\nSystem.out.println("Product: " + product);\n\n// Max\nint max = numbers.stream()\n    .reduce(Integer.MIN_VALUE, (a, b) -> a > b ? a : b);\nSystem.out.println("Max: " + max);\n\n// Min\nint min = numbers.stream()\n    .reduce(Integer.MAX_VALUE, (a, b) -> a < b ? a : b);\nSystem.out.println("Min: " + min);\n\n// Without identity (returns Optional)\nOptional<Integer> sumOptional = numbers.stream()\n    .reduce((a, b) -> a + b);\nsumOptional.ifPresent(s -> System.out.println("Sum optional: " + s));\n\n// Concatenate strings\nList<String> words = Arrays.asList("Hello", " ", "World", "!");\nString sentence = words.stream()\n    .reduce("", (a, b) -> a + b);\nSystem.out.println("Concatenated: " + sentence);\n\n// Find longest string\nList<String> names = Arrays.asList("Alice", "Bob", "Christopher", "David");\nOptional<String> longest = names.stream()\n    .reduce((a, b) -> a.length() > b.length() ? a : b);\nlongest.ifPresent(s -> System.out.println("Longest name: " + s));\n\n// Count with reduce (not efficient, just demo)\nlong count = numbers.stream()\n    .reduce(0, (cnt, n) -> cnt + 1, (c1, c2) -> c1 + c2);\nSystem.out.println("Count: " + count);',
